rComments: I just found out this prof is no longer at UofO and am totally bummed out. Took 2 classes with her and was hoping to take more. Not sure if she's still teaching but if you get a chance to take a class with her, do it. She's great!
A good class for those interested in improving writing skills however, she's definitely not a good professor. Too many pet peeves and not very helpful.

Very fair. Very helpful. The key to doing well is to read stoires, go to class, and if your every unsure go and see her during office hours. She basically spoon feeds you the course as long as you apply yourself.
Loved going to this class. Never missed one. Time flew by and discussion was always interesting. Angela was very helpful, fun and friendly. Tough marker but I learned alot.

Disliked. Loved the subject and looked forward to taking Children's Lit, and they switched her in as our prof last minute. Very condescending when talking to students, then gets mad when we don't talk enough. Goes through notes much too fast. Not the worst teacher out there, but I've had way better.

I grumbled about needing to take English in my first year; that is, until I met Dr. Deziel. She's a ton of fun - her classes are informal but informative, she's quick with e-mail replies, and she's genuinely a great person. I may well take English classes next year because of her. A true joy, and a highly recommended prof.
Good teacher, explains everything very very clear. BUT SHE IS A TOUGH MARKER, you NEED to do the reading or you will fail...

best prof in the world. only class where i actually got up for an 8:30 lecture. nice clothes. READ THE STORIES. she gives you an automatic 5% if you attend all classes. Pop quizzes were an easy 10% to get too. She's beautiful!
She is Beautiful!!!!! And She explains everything clear. I love her teaching and she is cute, helpful, easy and everything.

We love Angela, she's hilarious to watch and listen to. She's a ditzy person (she wrote 'overfedding' instead of overfeeding). She says 'umm' a lot but overall she's friendly and fun to imitate. Unintentionally set of fire alarm once. We hope we get her again!

For a person who doesn't normally like english...I really enjoyed this class. The discussions were interesting - its not like a high school type english course where you do various little assignments and drag through things and overanalyze. She is a very nice proff, and quite helpful.
Pretty boring course, prof needs a little more practice in teaching, very nice person though. She is extremely strict with writing assignments, but the final was pretty easy.

She was quick in answering questions, and her feedback was always helpful. She really needs to stop going over EVERY grammar exercise in class... it's not the fact that we don't KNOW the answer that keeps us from raising our hand, it's that we know it so well that going over comma splices for the 90th time is putting us to sleep.
She is a great teacher. She knows the course, and she is friendly. She is helpful when she marks work

Awesome teacher! Explains things well and is very organized. Material was somewhat boring but she was able to make it interesting. Very helpful and easy to talk to. Papers were easy if you did the readings and followed instructions.
my favorite class this semester which is sayign alot because i don't like english. Assignments were good, she put us in groups which was fun. seemed to really know the material.
this prof rocks my socks off (see she even taught me how to rhyme).  no one can argue. Angela is key to the english world.
nice person but i'm sorry, you're class is boooooorrrrrriiinnnggg!!!
No Comments
She isnt the greatest teacher, not very helpful and favours certain students.

approachable,funny&clear.straighforward grading,opportunities to up your mark.My essays are SO much better b/c of her.I got her class again,&haven't been disappointed. it might seem she asks a lot of you, but inthe end its b/c its prep for an assignment(a brainstorm she marks in time 4 writing essay,&gives good tips). lots of leway-do 3/5 asgn only

Very friendly and knowledgeable.  Very thorough in her analyses of the works looked at in class.  It will be hard to get a poor mark in her class, but she still leaves you with something new that you've learned when the class is finished.

Her lectures are very well prepared and she's really organized.  Also, takes lots of time to help you if you show up to office hours.  To whoever picked on her wardrobe: grow up! She was always carefully and professionally dressed, and even if you don't like it, it's not like it makes any difference to what you learned in her class.
Overall, a good prof.  Responds to questions pretty quickly, and helps if you ask for it.  Makes English fun, or at least as fun as it gets.  Excellent fashion sense!
She needs to learn that this is a class not a club and dress appropriately; it's difficult to take her seriously.

she made what could be a very boring class interesting and usefull. i agree that late penalty is harsh but she outlines it clearly before every assignment and is being fair to those of us who get things in on time. as long as you have a reason for screwing up she seems wiling to listen.

her tardy policy is tough--if you're 10 mins late, she immediately docks down points.  I mean it's understandable, but I lost a full grade just because  I missed my bus.  Most professors give students until the end of class to turn an assignment in...as long as it's in THAT day, why not?
Angela's a good cookie.
Well prepared lectures, decent delivery (although somewhat dull, due mostly to content).  Very helpful and accessible, and a fair marker.  A credit to the english department.

helpful in office hours and patient. funny which helps because the material is boring. gives lots of good feedback and is always smiling. i learned a lot but the grammar lectures are blah. to the person who wrote the last entry - i disagree and you should learn how to spell!!
Not very profesional
Sweet, smart and sexy.
I find her to be well-prepared and helpful, and she does make the material interesting.  Also, she seems to be helpful during office hours and friendly.

This class was boring because of the material, but she made it bearable. Sometimes it seems as though she was just reading form her notes the whole class. She makes you copy definitions every class. An ok. marker.
